SIMPLE: worship
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worship
<hw>Wor"ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>worshipe</ets>, <ets>wur⟦edh⟧scipe</ets>, AS.
<ets>weor⟦edh⟧scipe</ets>; <ets>weor⟦edh⟧</ets> worth +
<ets>-scipe</ets> -ship. See <er>Worth</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and
<er>-ship</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Excellence of character; dignity; worth;
worthiness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man of <qex>worship</qex> and honour.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Elfin, born of noble state,⟦br⟧
And muckle <qex>worship</qex> in his native land.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Honor; respect; civil deference.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of which great worth and <qex>worship</qex> may be won.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then shalt thou have <qex>worship</qex> in the presence of them
that sit at meat with thee.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xiv. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, a title of honor, used in addresses to
certain magistrates and others of rank or station.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My father desires your <qex>worships'</qex> company.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The act of paying divine honors to the Supreme
Being; religious reverence and homage; adoration, or acts of reverence,
paid to God, or a being viewed as God.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧God with idols in
their <xex>worship</xex> joined.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>worship</qex> of God is an eminent part of religion, and
prayer is a chief part of religious <qex>worship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Obsequious or submissive respect; extravagant
admiration; adoration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is your inky brows, your black silk hair,⟦br⟧
Your bugle eyeballs, nor your cheek of cream,⟦br⟧
That can my spirits to your <qex>worship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>An object of worship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In attitude and aspect formed to be⟦br⟧
At once the artist's <qex>worship</qex> and despair.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Devil worship</b></col>, <col><b>Fire
worship</b></col>, <col><b>Hero worship</b></col></mcol>, <cd>etc. See
under <er>Devil</er>, <er>Fire</er>, <er>Hero</er>, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worship</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Worship
<hw>Wor"ship</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Worshiped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> <conjf>Worshipped</conjf>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Worshiping</conjf> ⟦or⟧
<conjf>Worshipping</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To respect; to honor; to treat with civil
reverence.</def> <mark>[Obsoles.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our grave . . . shall have a tongueless mouth,⟦br⟧
Not <qex>worshiped</qex> with a waxen epitaph.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This holy image that is man God <qex>worshipeth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Foxe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pay divine honors to; to reverence with supreme
respect and veneration; to perform religious exercises in honor of; to
adore; to venerate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But God is to be <qex>worshiped</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When all our fathers <qex>worshiped</qex> stocks and stones.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To honor with extravagant love and extreme
submission, as a lover; to adore; to idolize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With bended knees I daily <qex>worship</qex> her.</q>
<rj><qau>Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To adore; revere; reverence; bow to;
honor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worship</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Worship
<hw>Wor"ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To perform acts of
homage or adoration; esp., to perform religious service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our fathers <qex>worshiped</qex> in this mountain; and ye say that
in Jerusalem is the place where men ought to <qex>worship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>John iv. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Was it for this I have loved . . . and <qex>worshiped</qex> in
silence?</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worshipability</ent>⟦br⟧
